LATEX (acronym for Latex) is a document preparation system for high-quality typesetting. It is widely used to typeset scientific and technical documents, such as books, articles, and mathematical papers. LATEX provides a user-friendly interface for creating documents with complex layouts and equations.

Fen is an acronym for the Fraction Environment of LATEX. The Fen environment provides a powerful way to typeset fractions, allowing you to typeset fractions of any size and type, from simple to complex fractions. You can use the Fen environment to typeset fractions in tables, equations, and text.

To use the Fen environment in your document, you will need to install the package called LATEX-Fen on your computer. You can find the package on the Internet or you can install it using the package manager of your operating system. Once installed, you can include the following code in your document:
\usepackage{lmodern}
\usepackage[utf8]{inputenc}
\usepackage{fencol}

